    </div>
    <h2>Low floor access</h2>
<p>All buses are able to kneel to reduce the step-up. Drivers are expected to pull in close to the kerb. If you need low-floor access and the driver has not already knelt the vehicle, just ask.</p>
<p>While there is a step and gap onto most Tube and Overground trains, we are introducing more low-floor trains, including on the Metropolitan, Hammersmith &amp; City, Circle and District lines.</p>
<p>Most taxis have an intermediate step and a seat that swivels out to make it easier to get in. Ask the driver if you want to use either of these.</p> 
 </div>
 <div>

<h2>Safety and security</h2>
<p>Your safety is important to us, and crime is at its lowest ever levels on London's transport network. </p>
<p>CCTV is used extensively across stations, piers, all buses and many trains. <a href="/corporate/privacy-and-cookies/cctv">Find out how we use CCTV</a>.</p>
</div>
 <div class="clearfix">
