        <img src="/cdn/static/cms/images/help-point_rdax_400x250.jpg" alt="Help points are on most platforms" />
        
        
        
    </div>
    <p>Passenger alarms on trains can be used to contact the
driver in an emergency. They are found next to doors and wheelchair spaces.
</p>
<p>Help points are available on most
platforms and in all ticket halls. They can be used to contact staff in an emergency, or to ask for help or information.
</p>
<p>If you feel unsafe or experience any incidents of crime
(including hate crime) or antisocial behavior talk to our staff
or the police.</p>
<p>You can also report hate crime by calling 101 or texting 61016</p>
